{"word":"σκίρον 1","slug":"σκίρον 1","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n94930\" key=\"ski/ron1\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">σκίρον</orth> [<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῐ], <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen></foreign>, <sense id=\"n94930.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the large white sunshade</tr_> which was held by the Eteobutadae over the heads of the priestess of Athena and the priests of Poseidon and Helios in the procession from the Athenian Acropolis to a place called <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Σκῖρον</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Σκίρον</foreign> (q.v.) in a festival of Athena (cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Σκίρα</foreign>), <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg2262.tlg001:23\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Lysimachid.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">23</biblScope> </bibl>; <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">white parasol</tr_> carried by the priest of Erechtheus in the festival of Athena <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Σκιράς</foreign> on the <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg2262.tlg001:12t\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12t</biblScope> </bibl>h of <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Σκιροφοριών</foreign>, Sch.<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg010.perseus-grc1:18\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ec.\">Ec.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}